
Richmond [7] Apr. 1781. Acknowledges a letter of this date with Genl. Spotswoods letter which is now returnd. In obedience to your reccomendation I have extended the Contract for Catridge Boxes and belts to 2000 More, judging the price reasonable, if the exchange can be adjusted by the price of Tobacco. Has written to the General on the subject of the exchange and allowed him to draw for a part of the Money in terms of his letter; encloses his letter to be forwarded when you write to him.
